Step 1: Calculate Debt to Equity Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, Total Liabilities can be found as:  
  Total Liabilities = Total Liabilities and Owner's Equity – Total Owner's Equity  
  = 21,098,887.48 – 16,056,497.85  
  = 5,042,389.63  
• Total Owner's Equity = 16,056,497.85  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = 5,042,389.63 / 16,056,497.85 ≈ 0.314, which rounds to 0.31  

Step 2: Calculate Net Profit Margin  
• From the income statement, Net Profit = 56,497.85 and Total Revenue = 547,392.30  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
  = (56,497.85 / 547,392.30) × 100%  
  ≈ 10.32%  

Step 3: Calculate Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio  
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -2,868,695.86 and Total Current Liabilities = 5,042,389.63  
• Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio = -2,868,695.86 / 5,042,389.63  
  ≈ -0.57  

Thus, the final answer in the requested JSON format is:

{"solution": {"Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.31", "Net Profit Margin": "10.32%", "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-0.57"}}
